    <p><span style="font-weight:400;">This article discusses the effect of the internet on customer’s intent to purchase. Before the internet, the customer’s knowledge of a product was mostly from the brand and price. The internet enabled find more information of a product through an infomediary. The infomediary reduced the search cost of the consumer leading to more informed purchases.</span></p>
