            Avi Goldfarb, Catherine Tucker<br />
        </span>
    </p>
    <p><span style="font-weight:400;">This paper goes over purchasing intent of people viewing online advertisements.Independently, obtrusive advertisements and targeted advertisements increase purchasing intent of the viewer. However, their study found that advertisements that are both targeted and obtrusive can decrease the purchasing intent of the viewer. The researchers believe that the combination effect is due to privacy concerns that the users have.</span></p>

